
## Objective
Learn how to investigate a network conversation between a client and a server using Wireshark's Follow TCP Stream feature.

## What I Learned
- A TCP stream displays the complete conversation between two devices.
- Follow TCP Stream isolates only the packets related to one communication.
- TLS encrypts the data, making the conversation unreadable in plain text.
- HTTP traffic can be viewed in plain text, while HTTPS traffic is protected by TLS.
- Following TCP streams helps security analysts investigate incidents more efficiently.

## Practical Exercise
- Captured network traffic in Wireshark.
- Applied a TLS filter.
- Followed a TCP stream.
- Observed an encrypted conversation between my computer and a remote server.
- Compared encrypted communication with plain HTTP traffic from previous lessons.

## Skills Practiced
- Wireshark
- TCP Stream Analysis
- TLS Traffic Analysis
- Network Investigation
- Packet Analysis

## Key Takeaway
Following TCP streams allows security analysts to focus on a single network conversation instead of manually reviewing thousands of packets, making investigations faster and more effective.
